{
  "answer": "**Kātyāyana Smṛti** (slug: `unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2`) discusses women's *strīdhana* (woman's separate property) primarily in Chapters 75–77, treating it as impartible estate not subject to division among heirs. A brief reference appears earlier in Chapter 72.[^1][^2][^3][^4]\n\n### Chapter 72: Impartible Properties (mention at K_877)\n*Strīdhana* is listed alongside wealth from valor or learning as not divisible at partition.[^5]\n\n### Chapter 75: Definition and Types (K_894–901)\nDefines *strīdhana* as six-fold: gifts before/at the nuptial fire (*adhyagni*, *adhyāvāhanika*), out of affection (*prītidatta*), bride-price (*śulka*), and subsequent gifts (*anvādheya*, *saudāyika*) from kin.[^6]\n\n### Chapter 76: Ownership and Disposition (K_902–916)\nDetails givers (father, mother, etc.), exclusions (conditional/fraudulent gifts), husband's limited rights, woman's independence (esp. over *saudāyika*), prohibitions on seizure by kin, and penalties.[^7]\n\n### Chapter 77: Heirs (K_917–920)\nOutlines succession: daughters first, then sons or kin; immovable gifts revert to brothers/parents in certain cases (e.g., Āsura marriage).[^8]\n\nThese prose sections embed numbered verses (K_###). For full context, read the chapters directly; no other chapters cover *strīdhana*.\n\n[^1]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 72, [full chapter](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/72/translation/).\n\n[^2]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 75, [full chapter](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/75/translation/).\n\n[^3]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 76, [full chapter](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/76/translation/).\n\n[^4]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 77, [full chapter](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/77/translation/).\n\n[^5]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 72, [paragraph](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/72/translation/#p-7aa195).\n\n[^6]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 75, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/75/translation/#p-b8596e).\n\n[^7]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 76, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/76/translation/#p-f86392).\n\n[^8]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 77, [paragraphs](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/77/translation/#p-8abcd6).",
